-- Goldman Sachs Writes Down Its CMC Markets Stake to Zero, Telegraph Reports
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   L a r k i n
-- 2010-12-05T07:51:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-05/goldman-writes-down-cmc-investment-to-zero-telegraph-reports.html
Goldman Sachs Group Inc.  has written
down its stake in CMC Markets Plc to almost zero three years
after making the 140 million pound ($221 million) investment,
the  Sunday Telegraph  said.  CMC founder  Peter Cruddas  is aware of the writedown, the
newspaper reported, citing an unidentified person close to the
situation.  Sophie Bullock, a spokeswoman in London for London for
Goldman Sachs, declined to comment on the report to Bloomberg
News today.   To contact the reporter on this story:
 Nicholas Larkin  in London at 
 nlarkin1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
